The upgrade-to-Pro banner is shown to free users when they are logged out. This can be determined from the following code snippet:

[2] File: app/core/components/preview-banner/preview-banner.ts (lines 8-30)
```ts
@Component({
  selector: 'app-preview-banner',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [AsyncPipe],
  templateUrl: './preview-banner.html',
  styleUrl: './preview-banner.css'
})
export class PreviewBanner {
  private bannerService = inject(BannerService);
  private planPickerService = inject(PlanPickerService);
  private router = inject(Router);

  visible$ = this.bannerService.visible$;

  upgradeToPro() {
    if (Capacitor.isNativePlatform()) {
      this.planPickerService.show();
      return;
    }
    this.router.navigate(['/pricing']);
  }
}
```

In the `upgradeToPro` method, it checks if the user is logged in using Capacitor's `isNativePlatform()` function. If not, it navigates to the `/pricing` route. This indicates that free users will see and be able to click on the upgrade-to-Pro banner to navigate to the pricing page.
